{
  "texts": [
    "In this study, we used a Gaussian kernel function for kernel density calculations.",
    "The form of the kernel function is expressed in Eq.",
    "(3): https://doi.org/10.1038/s40494-025-01806-8",
    "In the formula: f ðxÞ represents the density value at raster cell x, indicating the weighted density of social media check-in points at that location.",
    "n denotes the total number of points in the dataset (i.e., the total number of check-in points)."
  ]
}